responded: The bug is at this line in `Zend/zend_opcode.c`:
```c
1074| opline->op1.opline_num = op_array->try_catch_array[opline->op1.num].finally_op;
```
If `op_array->try_catch_array` is `NULL`, this will dereference a null pointer, causing a crash.

**Fix:**  
Add a check to ensure `op_array->try_catch_array` is not `NULL` and that `opline->op1.num` is within bounds (`op_array->last_try_catch > opline->op1.num`) before dereferencing.

Here is the patch:

```diff
--- a/Zend/zend_opcode.c
+++ b/Zend/zend_opcode.c
@@ -1073,7 +1073,13 @@
 			case ZEND_FAST_CALL:
-				opline->op1.opline_num = op_array->try_catch_array[opline->op1.num].finally_op;
-				ZEND_PASS_TWO_UPDATE_JMP_TARGET(op_array, opline, opline->op1);
-				break;
+				if (op_array->try_catch_array != NULL && opline->op1.num < op_array->last_try_catch) {
+					opline->op1.opline_num = op_array->try_catch_array[opline->op1.num].finally_op;
+					ZEND_PASS_TWO_UPDATE_JMP_TARGET(op_array, opline, opline->op1);
+				} else {
+					/* Defensive: set to 0 if invalid, or handle as needed */
+					opline->op1.opline_num = 0;
+				}
+				break;
```

